WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:58.994 --> 01:59.994
Dad...

02:03.999 --> 02:05.786
<i>Hey, sorry about the delay;</i>

02:05.876 --> 02:07.617
the storm at LaGuardia
was really bad.

02:07.711 --> 02:09.043
<i>It was no big deal.</i>

02:09.670 --> 02:11.537
I was just waiting
about an hour.

02:20.849 --> 02:22.761
This airport seems bigger now.

02:23.518 --> 02:24.958
When was the last time
you were here?

02:25.020 --> 02:26.727
Wasn't it like, Thanksgiving?

02:26.813 --> 02:28.554
Yeah... in '82.

03:02.140 --> 03:03.847
(Woman) <i>Are they here?</i>

03:05.310 --> 03:07.597
[dog barking]

03:19.991 --> 03:21.232
<i>Aw... Landry?</i>

03:21.326 --> 03:22.326
<i>Don't let him out?</i>

03:22.411 --> 03:25.245
<i>My best boy?
I have missed you so much.</i>

03:26.248 --> 03:28.991
<i>- Dad, you got it?
- Yep?</i>

03:29.084 --> 03:31.747
- Oh, Adrian.
- Hey, Mom.

03:34.089 --> 03:36.331
Goodness gracious,
you've gotten so thin!

03:36.425 --> 03:38.087
Yeah, he had a stomach flu.

03:38.176 --> 03:39.758
- Are you alright now?
- Yeah, I'm fine.

03:39.845 --> 03:42.053
I'll take this big ol' bag
of rocks in your room.

03:42.139 --> 03:44.131
Andrew?
Andrew, your brother's here.

03:45.851 --> 03:48.059
Hey, Andrew.

03:49.271 --> 03:51.228
Wow, man,
you've gotten so tall.

03:53.650 --> 03:54.936
Hey, can I get a hug?

03:57.112 --> 03:59.650
Oh, Andrew...
He's just being a little shy.

03:59.740 --> 04:01.384
- It's fine, Mom.
- He's very excited to see you.

04:01.408 --> 04:03.400
- It's fine...
- Andrew!

04:04.995 --> 04:06.987
<i>We thank you, Father,
for bringing Adrian</i>

04:07.080 --> 04:09.117
<i>back home safe and sound
to celebrate</i>

04:09.207 --> 04:11.324
this blessed holiday with us.

04:11.418 --> 04:15.082
We pray that You will
watch over and guide him,

04:15.172 --> 04:18.415
as You have watched over
and guided all of us.

04:18.507 --> 04:19.839
Amen.

04:19.926 --> 04:21.212
(All) Amen.

04:22.179 --> 04:23.465
I made all your favorites.

04:23.555 --> 04:25.968
Wow, this looks
really delicious, Mom.

04:31.980 --> 04:33.187
Still playing football Andrew?

04:33.273 --> 04:34.605
He quit last year.

04:35.984 --> 04:37.065
I kinda sucked at it.

04:37.152 --> 04:39.018
No, that's not true now.

04:39.112 --> 04:41.229
Coach Jennings said
you have great potential.

04:43.366 --> 04:46.825
Andrew is the vice president
of the drama club now.

04:47.412 --> 04:48.744
Wow, is that right?

04:49.289 --> 04:51.201
He was in
<i>Arsenic and Old Lace</i> recently.

04:51.291 --> 04:52.907
I was the lead.

04:53.210 --> 04:55.793
You were a very
convincing older man.

04:55.879 --> 04:58.212
And he got the biggest applause.

04:58.298 --> 05:01.006
He needs to speak up
is what he needs to do.

05:01.092 --> 05:03.129
He mumbled through
most of his lines.

05:03.220 --> 05:05.052
I could barely
understand him half the time.

05:09.100 --> 05:11.262
Sorry I missed it, buddy.

05:11.353 --> 05:13.185
I'm sure you were brilliant,

05:13.271 --> 05:15.183
you wouldn't be cast
as a lead otherwise.

05:19.402 --> 05:22.520
Are you still at that same
place, the ad agency?

05:22.614 --> 05:23.445
Yep.

05:23.532 --> 05:25.398
You've been there
a long time. Still like it?

05:26.284 --> 05:29.243
Yeah, it's been three years.
I still like it a lot.

05:30.914 --> 05:32.155
Have you guys seen the

05:32.249 --> 05:34.241
<i>Crunchy Chocolate Puffs</i>
commercial

05:34.334 --> 05:35.950
that's playing right now?

05:36.044 --> 05:37.376
Oh, yeah.

05:37.462 --> 05:38.998
You worked on that?

05:39.089 --> 05:40.455
I wrote parts of it, yeah.

05:41.174 --> 05:42.415
I saw it.

05:42.509 --> 05:43.716
It was lame.

05:44.970 --> 05:46.586
Andrew, that wasn't very nice.

05:47.597 --> 05:48.883
No, he's right, Mom.

05:50.475 --> 05:51.716
It's kinda lame.

05:55.522 --> 05:56.888
How are your roommates?

05:58.066 --> 05:59.227
They're great.

06:01.194 --> 06:03.186
Um, did they go home
for Christmas too?

06:03.280 --> 06:04.111
Mm-hmm.

06:04.197 --> 06:05.358
Where are they from?

06:07.409 --> 06:11.028
Brandon is from New Jersey,
and Leo is from Ohio.

06:11.788 --> 06:14.531
I think I talked to Leo
on the phone once

06:14.624 --> 06:15.785
when you weren't there.

06:15.876 --> 06:17.287
He sounded very nice.

06:20.297 --> 06:22.710
I just can't understand
how three grown men

06:22.799 --> 06:23.710
can still live together.

06:23.800 --> 06:25.587
It's like y'all
are back in college.

06:25.677 --> 06:28.010
Dale, the rents are much
more expensive there.

06:28.096 --> 06:29.883
I'm aware of that it's just...

06:29.973 --> 06:33.967
This pot roast, Mom,
is as good as I remember it.

06:34.060 --> 06:35.972
I've literally had dreams
about your cooking,

06:36.062 --> 06:37.062
I miss it that much.

06:37.147 --> 06:38.809
Thank you, honey,
that's very sweet.

06:39.149 --> 06:40.481
<i>Hey, can you smell Georgie?</i>

06:42.360 --> 06:46.024
Yeah? I think you two
would like each other.

06:52.954 --> 06:54.035
<i>Knock, knock?</i>

06:54.122 --> 06:57.991
Hey... Mom, I'm so full
I can't have another bite.

06:58.084 --> 06:59.825
Come on, will you please
eat this cake?

06:59.920 --> 07:01.627
Your brother's going
to eat it, otherwise,

07:01.713 --> 07:03.670
and all the sugar is not good
for his complexion.

07:03.757 --> 07:05.214
Oh, poor guy.

07:07.469 --> 07:08.469
Alright.

07:10.430 --> 07:14.174
It's... it's really good.
It's very good, Mom.

07:15.268 --> 07:18.136
You know, your Dad wanted to
turn this room into storage

07:18.229 --> 07:22.064
but I just didn't have the heart
to take out all your stuff.

07:24.402 --> 07:29.113
And also I like to
sleep in here sometimes.

07:31.326 --> 07:32.862
You know
how your Dad snores.

07:34.788 --> 07:35.824
I haven't missed that.

07:37.040 --> 07:39.032
I hope you're not
too bothered by Andrew.

07:39.292 --> 07:40.292
No, I'm not.

07:42.796 --> 07:44.503
I know he's still mad at me.

07:45.423 --> 07:48.211
I ran into Carly yesterday
at the store.

07:48.301 --> 07:50.793
She had no idea
you were coming to town.

07:50.887 --> 07:52.970
I thought you guys talk to
each other once in awhile.

07:53.056 --> 07:54.672
Uh, no. It's been awhile.

07:55.600 --> 07:56.600
I just got busy.

07:57.894 --> 08:00.102
Well, it turns out
she moved to Dallas.

08:00.188 --> 08:01.019
She's got a job there.

08:01.106 --> 08:02.106
Yeah, I heard that.

08:04.818 --> 08:07.481
Her Dad had
a heart attack recently,

08:07.570 --> 08:08.435
did you know that?

08:08.530 --> 08:11.238
I didn't know that. Is he OK?

08:12.075 --> 08:16.991
He's recovering, but Carly's
at home helping out her Mom.

08:18.123 --> 08:19.739
She gave me
her new phone number

08:19.833 --> 08:21.745
if you wanna give her a call.

08:21.835 --> 08:22.835
OK.

08:25.880 --> 08:27.746
Christmas wasn't the same
without you.

08:30.218 --> 08:31.925
I'm really glad
you made it back this year.

08:32.429 --> 08:33.840
Yeah, me too, Mom.

08:39.309 --> 08:41.677
Well, you should get some rest.
You must be exhausted.

08:41.770 --> 08:42.770
Yeah.

08:43.606 --> 08:44.972
And eat this cake!

08:45.066 --> 08:46.853
OK! Fine.

08:48.486 --> 08:50.603
- Goodnight, honey.
- Goodnight, Mom.

08:56.161 --> 08:57.161
Landry?

08:59.289 --> 09:00.289
Landry...

09:09.215 --> 09:10.672
It's our little secret, buddy.

09:11.259 --> 09:14.423
Oh, you are hungry!

09:32.197 --> 09:34.439
Shhh... Stop.

09:38.495 --> 09:43.035
Landry, you're such
a bed hog, get off...

09:57.222 --> 09:59.384
(Radio) <i>You're listening to</i>
The Word <i>with Dave Hewitt.</i>

10:00.016 --> 10:03.430
<i>Right before the break,
I was talking about Santa Claus.</i>

10:03.520 --> 10:06.012
<i>How a lot of us,
myself included,</i>

10:06.106 --> 10:07.958
<i>have accepted the dominance
of Santa in Christmas.</i>

10:07.982 --> 10:10.065
- Good morning.
- Mornin'.

10:10.151 --> 10:10.982
Morning.

10:11.069 --> 10:12.296
<i>But Santa Claus
has distracted us...</i>

10:12.320 --> 10:13.686
How'd you sleep?

10:13.780 --> 10:15.646
I slept great.

10:15.740 --> 10:18.153
I hope you're hungry because
breakfast will be ready soon.

10:18.409 --> 10:19.320
Can I do anything?

10:19.410 --> 10:21.072
No, just, have some coffee.

10:23.081 --> 10:26.290
<i>The lie about Santa Claus
may not be a big deal.</i>

10:26.376 --> 10:28.709
<i>I certainly don't think
that it is.</i>

10:28.795 --> 10:32.709
<i>But there are many other lies,
in our society,</i>

10:32.799 --> 10:34.586
<i>that do a lot more damage.</i>

10:35.218 --> 10:36.334
You want more coffee, Dad?

10:36.427 --> 10:38.259
Hmm? No, no. I'm good.

10:41.724 --> 10:43.966
(Radio continues) <i>I'll get more
into this in a minute,</i>

10:44.060 --> 10:47.804
<i>because what I'm ultimately
getting at is the truth.</i>

10:47.897 --> 10:50.731
<i>The church,
our place of worship,</i>

10:50.817 --> 10:53.104
<i>is the foundation of truth.</i>

10:53.194 --> 10:56.107
<i>When we're there having
fellowship with each other,</i>

10:56.197 --> 10:58.109
<i>we hear the truth.</i>

10:58.199 --> 11:01.237
<i>But, when we're not
at the church,</i>

11:01.327 --> 11:07.073
<i>we are surrounded by
so many pervasive lies.</i>

11:07.167 --> 11:12.003
<i>Remember what Jesus said
in John 8:32?</i>

11:12.088 --> 11:14.250
<i>Then you will know the truth,</i>

11:14.340 --> 11:16.832
<i>and the truth
will set you free...</i>

11:16.926 --> 11:19.839
Honey? Are you OK?

11:20.180 --> 11:22.217
Yeah. Yeah, no I'm fine.
I'm just waking up.

11:26.936 --> 11:27.936
[knocking on door]

11:32.275 --> 11:33.275
Andrew?

11:34.110 --> 11:35.146
Andrew...

11:35.945 --> 11:36.856
What?

11:36.946 --> 11:38.232
Mom wants you up for breakfast.

11:47.832 --> 11:48.743
Give it back.

11:48.833 --> 11:49.833
Sorry.

11:52.545 --> 11:53.956
Hey um...

11:55.548 --> 11:58.006
I wanna apologize to you for um,

11:58.092 --> 12:00.070
you not being able to come
to New York to visit me.

12:00.094 --> 12:02.552
I know you were really
bummed about that.

12:02.639 --> 12:04.596
I just...

12:04.682 --> 12:07.800
something came up and I couldn't
get any time off so...

12:12.273 --> 12:13.980
Hey, what are you
listening to nowadays?

12:30.333 --> 12:33.246
Is that Madonna? Since when
were you into Madonna?

12:36.047 --> 12:39.165
Hey, um, I was at her last show,

12:39.259 --> 12:41.000
at Radio City Music Hall.

12:42.095 --> 12:45.634
Wait, you went
to the <i>Virgin</i> Tour?

12:45.723 --> 12:48.056
Yeah! Leo got us
front row tickets.

12:48.142 --> 12:49.053
No way.

12:49.143 --> 12:52.011
It was so much fun, man.
We had such a blast.

12:53.773 --> 12:58.108
I had her other album too but...

12:59.487 --> 13:02.230
Dad found it in my backpack
and threw it away.

13:02.323 --> 13:03.359
Really?

13:03.449 --> 13:05.941
He's thrown away
a bunch of tapes.

13:06.953 --> 13:11.914
I had a Bryan Adams poster
but he tore it off the wall.

13:12.000 --> 13:16.995
There was a sermon at church
about "secular music."

13:17.880 --> 13:19.997
That's nothing new, Andrew,

13:20.091 --> 13:22.959
they'll always find ways
to make that stuff up.

13:23.928 --> 13:26.966
Yeah, well, people around here
don't think it's made up.

13:30.476 --> 13:33.344
You know Mr. Thompson
from down the road?

13:33.438 --> 13:35.395
- Yeah?
- He has all the records.

13:35.481 --> 13:37.518
Oh, yeah.
He has an amazing collection.

13:37.984 --> 13:41.648
He <i>had</i> an amazing collection.

13:41.738 --> 13:45.482
He had Pastor John over and they
burned them all in his backyard.

13:45.575 --> 13:47.817
You could see the smoke
from blocks away.

13:47.910 --> 13:50.493
The fire department had to come
and put it out.

13:55.543 --> 13:57.000
Do you think I'm ugly?

13:57.086 --> 14:00.955
I mean, like, if you weren't
my brother and all.

14:01.049 --> 14:03.382
Andrew, why would you ask that?

14:04.260 --> 14:08.300
Well, I don't know.
The kids at school, they um...

14:09.390 --> 14:11.052
They call me pizza face.

14:13.436 --> 14:15.894
Tommy Clements said
that his sister said

14:15.980 --> 14:17.642
that there's no way
we're related

14:17.732 --> 14:20.349
'cause you're so much
better looking than me.

14:21.277 --> 14:23.234
You're not ugly, OK?

14:23.321 --> 14:27.315
I had really bad skin too.
It goes away after a few years.

14:28.659 --> 14:31.743
Kids can just be assholes.

14:32.205 --> 14:36.916
Also Tommy's older sister,
Susie, was such a bitch.

14:37.001 --> 14:38.162
And no one liked her

14:38.252 --> 14:39.813
because she tried way too hard
to be cool,

14:39.837 --> 14:41.544
so he's probably the same.

14:42.256 --> 14:45.169
You just said the A-word
and the B-word.

14:46.010 --> 14:47.592
Yeah, I'm gonna
call you the A-word

14:47.678 --> 14:49.590
if you don't get up
for breakfast!

14:49.680 --> 14:52.514
It's pancake day!
We eat pancakes!

14:52.600 --> 14:53.511
We can have pancakes...

14:53.601 --> 14:56.093
<i>Knock it off?
Breakfast is ready?</i>

14:56.187 --> 14:57.098
That was your fault.

14:57.188 --> 14:58.053
What?

14:58.147 --> 14:59.147
Yep, all your fault!

15:00.191 --> 15:01.523
<i>Give it all you got now?
Come on?</i>

15:01.984 --> 15:02.984
I'm trying...

15:04.320 --> 15:05.481
So are you seeing anyone?

15:07.115 --> 15:09.357
Barely have time for myself,
much less anyone else, Mom.

15:10.118 --> 15:12.576
'Cause y'know I spoke with Carly

15:12.662 --> 15:14.870
and I think she's
still on the market.

15:14.956 --> 15:17.198
- Mom.
- What?

15:17.291 --> 15:18.827
I was very fond of her.

15:19.544 --> 15:21.877
Yeah, well, Dad wasn't.

15:22.880 --> 15:25.167
That's a different story,
and you know why.

15:27.260 --> 15:28.592
Can I borrow your car?

15:28.678 --> 15:30.158
I need to get
some stuff at the store.

15:30.221 --> 15:32.838
Sure, um, can you
drop me off at the church?

15:32.932 --> 15:34.368
I'm volunteering for
the afternoon service.

15:34.392 --> 15:35.223
Yeah, sure.

15:35.309 --> 15:36.829
Will you pick up
some stuff for me too?

15:36.853 --> 15:37.853
I'll make you a list

15:37.937 --> 15:39.777
and you can just get the money
out of my purse.

15:39.814 --> 15:42.431
No, no, no just make
the list, Mom, I got it.

15:42.525 --> 15:43.436
It's so close!

15:43.526 --> 15:46.269
It's not just about strength;
it's about leverage, right?

15:46.362 --> 15:48.775
So turn tha...
turn that wrist, go on.

15:49.198 --> 15:50.780
There ya go. There ya go!

15:52.452 --> 15:53.909
- Yes!
- See?

15:53.995 --> 15:55.406
- OK!
- That was good work.

15:55.496 --> 15:56.890
So you have to do it
with the wrist?

15:56.914 --> 15:58.496
- Yeah, you feel it?
- Yeah.

15:59.542 --> 16:01.955
With your size you're gonna
need some leverage, alright?

16:02.420 --> 16:04.082
<i>Just checking in on Georgie.
Is he OK?</i>

16:06.048 --> 16:07.048
Did he stop throwing up?

16:08.301 --> 16:09.917
Well, good, OK, that's good.

16:11.012 --> 16:12.173
How are you doing?

16:14.056 --> 16:15.638
[chuckling]

16:17.268 --> 16:18.268
Oh, man.

16:21.481 --> 16:22.722
Uh, no I haven't.

16:25.776 --> 16:27.187
I just got here, Brandon.

16:31.908 --> 16:32.908
Yeah.

16:35.077 --> 16:36.238
Yeah, I know.

16:38.372 --> 16:39.863
That's really rich
coming from you.

16:42.251 --> 16:43.367
What, you just...

16:43.461 --> 16:46.044
You don't even talk
to your own family anymore!

16:47.507 --> 16:48.507
No!

16:48.591 --> 16:50.583
So stop telling me
what I should do!

16:58.226 --> 17:00.058
It's alright.
I'm sorry, Brandon.

17:00.144 --> 17:02.477
I just, don't really
wanna talk about this.

17:03.523 --> 17:04.638
Um...

17:05.148 --> 17:07.857
OK, I'll call you back
in a couple days, alright?

17:07.944 --> 17:09.935
Just don't worry about me, OK?

17:11.030 --> 17:12.271
And um...

17:12.365 --> 17:14.231
Give Georgie
lots of kisses for me.

17:16.035 --> 17:17.070
Alright. Bye.

17:43.271 --> 17:44.432
It's declined.

17:45.189 --> 17:46.896
Uh, can you try that again?

17:51.362 --> 17:53.399
Yeah, it's still
not going through.

17:53.489 --> 17:56.027
Um, OK, do you take Diner's?

17:56.784 --> 17:57.865
No.

17:58.536 --> 18:01.495
Alright, I'll just
pay cash then. That's fine.

18:04.250 --> 18:05.250
Here you go.

18:07.336 --> 18:09.043
Hey, Lester!

18:09.130 --> 18:10.792
Adrian Lester!
Ha! I thought that was you.

18:10.881 --> 18:11.962
Hey...

18:14.427 --> 18:17.261
Oh, Marc, we went to
Arlington Heights together.

18:17.346 --> 18:19.383
Yeah, yeah, hey.

18:20.266 --> 18:21.928
Did you move back to Fort Worth?

18:22.018 --> 18:25.261
No, sorry, I um, I'm just...
I'm home for the holidays.

18:26.272 --> 18:27.513
Do you work here?

18:27.607 --> 18:30.099
Yeah, I'm the Assistant Manager.

18:31.777 --> 18:32.938
That's great.

18:34.113 --> 18:35.979
Hey, do you want
a fresh pumpkin pie?

18:36.073 --> 18:37.814
I could hook you up.

18:38.451 --> 18:39.451
That's alright...

18:39.535 --> 18:41.697
No you gotta try ours,
they're the best.

18:41.787 --> 18:44.074
Wait right here, alright?
It'll take me one second.

18:44.165 --> 18:45.246
Alright.

19:01.474 --> 19:02.474
Hey!

19:03.225 --> 19:04.136
Hey.

19:04.226 --> 19:05.137
Sorry, I didn't know...

19:05.227 --> 19:06.968
I'll just put this right here
on your bag.

19:07.021 --> 19:08.261
How much do I owe you for this?

19:08.314 --> 19:10.806
Oh, no, it's on the house,
perks of the job.

19:13.235 --> 19:16.569
Uh, were you two years
ahead of me in school?

19:17.114 --> 19:18.400
Yeah.

19:18.491 --> 19:20.232
You were on
the football team, right?

19:20.326 --> 19:21.612
Go Yellow Jackets!

19:22.495 --> 19:23.861
I was a lot heftier then.

19:24.372 --> 19:26.614
Marcus. Marcus Peterson. Right?

19:27.333 --> 19:31.122
Yeah, I went by Marc
after I graduated.

19:31.212 --> 19:32.919
Marcus just sounds
so dorky you know?

19:34.465 --> 19:36.401
It's funny what dropping
two letters from your name

19:36.425 --> 19:37.791
can do for your self-image.

19:43.391 --> 19:45.303
Listen...

19:45.393 --> 19:47.510
I don't wanna pretend
like nothing happened before.

19:49.230 --> 19:51.722
I wasn't very nice
to a lot of people in school.

19:51.816 --> 19:55.435
And uh, I know I wasn't
very nice to you.

19:58.989 --> 20:01.231
I know it's not an excuse but,

20:01.325 --> 20:03.362
I was going through
a lot of stuff at home

20:03.452 --> 20:05.239
and I took it out on you guys.

20:05.329 --> 20:08.868
Y'know it was a really
long time ago. But...

