to freak out.

29:13.502 --> 29:16.119
A hundred dollars
to Sound Warehouse?

29:16.213 --> 29:17.329
Yeah.

29:17.422 --> 29:20.881
Yeah, so now you can get
whatever tapes you want.

29:20.968 --> 29:22.459
You just-
You have to hide them well.

29:23.470 --> 29:24.586
That's awesome.

29:25.472 --> 29:26.303
Thank you.

29:26.390 --> 29:28.006
Yeah, man, Merry Christmas.

29:28.100 --> 29:29.100
Merry Christmas.

29:30.018 --> 29:31.350
Praise!

29:31.436 --> 29:32.301
Everybody...

29:32.396 --> 29:33.432
Praise!

29:33.522 --> 29:34.854
You just gotta...

29:34.940 --> 29:36.476
Praise! Woo!

29:38.777 --> 29:40.380
<i>I just wanna see
what it looks like on you.</i>

29:40.404 --> 29:42.145
It's a little warm today, hun.

29:42.239 --> 29:44.151
Quit whining and just
put it on for a minute.

29:45.951 --> 29:47.067
Come on.

29:52.416 --> 29:53.952
Alright...

29:54.042 --> 29:55.123
Turn around.

29:56.044 --> 29:57.455
Wow! See, how handsome!

29:58.338 --> 30:00.000
Hey, I'm gonna
take Landry for a walk.

30:00.090 --> 30:01.206
OK.

30:17.858 --> 30:21.147
♪

30:43.050 --> 30:44.666
[sobbing]
I don't know what to do.

30:46.428 --> 30:47.544
Oh, God...

30:59.900 --> 31:01.311
I miss you so much.

31:31.223 --> 31:32.304
<i>Hello?</i>

31:33.016 --> 31:33.847
<i>Hello?</i>

31:33.934 --> 31:35.425
Hey Carly, it's Adrian.

31:38.355 --> 31:39.516
<i>Well, well.</i>

31:42.150 --> 31:43.266
Merry Christmas.

31:43.360 --> 31:44.521
<i>Right...</i>

31:45.320 --> 31:48.063
<i>Y'know I wasn't
counting on hearing from you.</i>

31:51.910 --> 31:53.151
Hey, how's your Dad?

31:53.245 --> 31:55.487
I'm really sorry to hear
what happened to him.

31:57.124 --> 31:59.036
<i>Right, um.
He's doing a lot better.</i>

31:59.126 --> 32:00.583
<i>Thank you for asking.</i>

32:00.669 --> 32:03.161
<i>Hopes to go back to work
after the holidays.</i>

32:03.255 --> 32:04.416
OK, that's good.

32:07.259 --> 32:09.171
Tell him I said hey
when you get a chance.

32:09.511 --> 32:10.627
<i>Yeah.</i>

32:14.724 --> 32:16.590
Hey, guess who
I ran into yesterday?

32:17.686 --> 32:19.427
Marcus fucking Peterson.

32:24.067 --> 32:25.228
Carly...

32:29.281 --> 32:30.897
Carly, are you really
this mad at me?

32:37.289 --> 32:39.030
<i>Did he give you any free shit?</i>

32:41.918 --> 32:44.080
Yeah he gave me
a pumpkin pie, actually.

32:45.464 --> 32:46.704
Why? Did he give you something?

32:47.466 --> 32:48.798
<i>Yeah.</i>

32:48.884 --> 32:50.404
<i>He gave me a fucking
rotisserie chicken</i>

32:50.469 --> 32:52.051
<i>when I was there with my Mom.</i>

32:52.137 --> 32:53.878
<i>It was so weird.</i>

32:53.972 --> 32:55.634
<i>I guess he's just
trying to make amends.</i>

32:56.683 --> 32:59.221
<i>Y'know, he's a changed man,
praise the Lord.</i>

33:00.228 --> 33:01.264
<i>Chicken was good though.</i>

33:01.354 --> 33:02.390
Yeah, so was the pie.

33:07.194 --> 33:09.311
Uh, are you busy?

33:09.404 --> 33:11.111
Uh, it would be
really nice to see you.

33:16.578 --> 33:19.116
<i>Y'know I live in Dallas now,
so...</i>

33:20.081 --> 33:21.081
OK, uh...

33:22.375 --> 33:23.786
I can borrow my Mom's car.

33:23.877 --> 33:25.869
You're only like,
45 minutes away.

33:25.962 --> 33:28.202
<i>Alright, well I have to get
ready for this thing tonight.</i>

33:29.299 --> 33:30.619
What's you're...
What's the thing?

33:32.010 --> 33:33.922
(Carly on stage)
How's everyone doing tonight?

33:34.012 --> 33:35.878
[applause]

33:35.972 --> 33:37.053
Alright.

33:38.433 --> 33:39.969
My name is Carly.

33:40.060 --> 33:47.479
But my Korean name is
Jeong Ki-bum Choi Young-soon.

33:47.567 --> 33:49.399
Right so,
just please call me Carly.

33:50.529 --> 33:51.986
Uh...

33:52.072 --> 33:54.064
Growing up in school,
I didn't think that I was

33:54.157 --> 33:57.400
any different from
any of the other students,

33:57.494 --> 33:59.861
until one day, in 6th grade,

33:59.955 --> 34:02.914
in history class we're learning
about World War Il.

34:02.999 --> 34:05.662
Madeline, the most
popular girl in school,

34:05.752 --> 34:08.290
stands up during the lesson,
points at me,

34:08.380 --> 34:11.293
and calls me a "dirty Jap."

34:11.382 --> 34:12.873
[Audience groans]

34:12.967 --> 34:14.333
Yeah, horrible, right?

34:14.969 --> 34:16.427
It's racist! It's just, like,

34:16.513 --> 34:18.721
assuming that
we're all the same.

34:18.806 --> 34:21.424
Y'know I'm Korean-American.
I'm very proud and I...

34:21.518 --> 34:23.851
thought it was important
to explain that to her.

34:23.937 --> 34:26.350
So the next day
I went to school...

34:26.438 --> 34:28.351
dressed in...

34:28.440 --> 34:31.809
traditional Korean garb,
which I...

34:31.902 --> 34:34.987
quite kindly explained to her
was called a Hanbok.

34:36.283 --> 34:38.024
And then I
kicked her fucking ass.

34:38.868 --> 34:40.109
Yes!

34:40.203 --> 34:41.364
Yeah, kicked her...

34:42.080 --> 34:44.288
Ass! Felt so good.

34:44.833 --> 34:47.746
But y'know what,
I do not condone violence.

34:47.835 --> 34:50.543
No, looking back
I feel pretty bad about it.

34:50.630 --> 34:54.123
But I thought it was important
to teach her the lesson,

34:54.217 --> 34:58.131
that there's a difference
between a "dirty Jap"...

34:58.221 --> 35:00.508
and a motherfucking "gook!"

35:01.266 --> 35:02.427
Thank you. Yeah.

35:03.184 --> 35:04.015
Thanks.

35:04.102 --> 35:05.764
[crowd laughs, applauds]

35:09.190 --> 35:10.021
Hey!

35:10.108 --> 35:11.189
Hey.

35:11.276 --> 35:13.142
Aw, man, you were hilarious!

35:13.236 --> 35:16.354
Thanks. Yeah thanks,
I'm still working out the jokes.

35:17.073 --> 35:18.439
It's really, really good.

35:18.533 --> 35:22.152
My cheeks are a little sore
from smiling so much.

35:22.245 --> 35:24.407
Um, do you want a drink?
I'll get the first round.

35:24.497 --> 35:25.328
Please.

35:25.415 --> 35:26.872
Hey, Gene,
can I have a vodka soda?

35:27.375 --> 35:28.866
And I'll have a gin and tonic.

35:34.132 --> 35:35.132
I don't know I just,

35:35.175 --> 35:37.132
started taking some
improv classes for fun.

35:37.218 --> 35:40.711
A coworker of mine
has been doing it for awhile

35:40.805 --> 35:43.172
and she suggested
that I give it a go.

35:43.266 --> 35:45.007
And y'know what, I just, um,

35:45.101 --> 35:46.683
I find it really liberating.

35:46.770 --> 35:49.250
You get to say all the shit that
you wouldn't say in real life.

35:50.440 --> 35:51.556
That's really cool.

35:52.442 --> 35:54.229
I just never...

35:54.319 --> 35:56.481
Never would have
pictured you doing this.

35:57.364 --> 35:58.775
It's awesome.

35:58.865 --> 36:00.948
Yeah, well, I'm still
very much an amateur.

36:03.119 --> 36:05.987
No, Carly, you're actually
really good at this.

36:06.373 --> 36:09.537
Thanks. My parents don't
even know that I'm doing it.

36:09.626 --> 36:12.619
I mean, if they knew that I
was doing stand-up in front of

36:12.712 --> 36:14.874
a bunch of drunks
in this part of town,

36:15.590 --> 36:17.350
Fuck, my Dad
would have another heart attack.

36:19.427 --> 36:22.170
And, y'know it's the whole
reason why I moved to Dallas.

36:22.263 --> 36:23.925
To get them off my back.

36:27.352 --> 36:29.514
Wish I had the balls
to do what you did though.

36:29.604 --> 36:31.937
You uh, you did it.
You left fucking Texas.

36:32.023 --> 36:33.559
You went for it.

36:33.650 --> 36:35.186
Look at you now.

36:35.276 --> 36:37.063
Making waves on Madison Avenue.

36:37.153 --> 36:38.985
Oh my God,
is that what my Mom said?

36:40.407 --> 36:42.114
Oh man, uh...

36:43.535 --> 36:45.527
Yeah, I'm...

36:45.620 --> 36:48.579
I'm still not making
any money and uh...

36:48.665 --> 36:52.079
I live in uh,
the same crappy neighborhood.

36:52.168 --> 36:53.784
I've been mugged three times.

36:53.878 --> 36:55.915
Wow, sounds like
you're living the dream.

36:57.340 --> 37:00.083
Yeah, no, this year has actually
been really rough for me.

37:05.473 --> 37:06.930
Well, if there's nothing else,

37:07.016 --> 37:09.929
this shitty year is about
to come to an end.

37:10.019 --> 37:12.557
So here is to 1986.

37:13.648 --> 37:16.982
May this new year,
give us a fucking break.

37:17.068 --> 37:18.068
Yeah, cheers to that.

37:22.115 --> 37:23.759
You don't have to go home
right away, do you?

37:23.783 --> 37:26.025
- You can hang out?
- Yes! What am I, 15?

37:26.119 --> 37:28.031
I don't know, man,
you always had curfews.

37:28.538 --> 37:30.074
What do you have in mind?

37:30.165 --> 37:31.765
I'm gonna take you
to this bitchin' club.

37:34.169 --> 37:37.879
♪

39:04.843 --> 39:08.052
[music plays in background]

39:09.138 --> 39:10.219
- Hey.
- Hey.

39:10.306 --> 39:11.137
Do you want some wine?

39:11.224 --> 39:13.056
Uh, no I'm good.

39:32.412 --> 39:34.028
We used to
do this all the time.

39:41.421 --> 39:42.502
Yeah, Carly, I'm-

39:44.632 --> 39:46.168
I, I really just wanna hang out.

39:47.010 --> 39:48.010
OK?

40:16.664 --> 40:18.155
[turns music off]

40:30.970 --> 40:32.586
Why did you stop calling me?

40:35.141 --> 40:37.383
I left you
so many fucking messages

40:37.477 --> 40:39.343
and you just
checked out on me.

40:43.274 --> 40:44.481
Yeah, I know.

40:49.864 --> 40:50.864
Hey.

40:53.117 --> 40:54.608
Adrian, please look at me.

40:56.663 --> 40:57.663
Please.

40:59.457 --> 41:02.074
What's going on? What's wrong?

41:03.002 --> 41:04.834
Nothing.

41:04.921 --> 41:06.708
Can I actually get water?

41:40.248 --> 41:41.248
Are you happy?

41:43.459 --> 41:45.371
Um...

41:45.461 --> 41:47.544
Yeah, I'm doing fine.
How have you been?

41:49.007 --> 41:50.088
Good.

41:51.217 --> 41:52.537
Are you seeing anyone
in New York?

41:54.512 --> 41:55.673
Uh, no I'm not.

41:57.223 --> 41:58.304
Are you seeing anyone?

41:59.976 --> 42:00.887
Adrian, I'm...

42:00.977 --> 42:03.060
Carly, the reason
I didn't call you back...

42:06.983 --> 42:08.440
I went there to start over.

42:11.487 --> 42:13.149
I really needed a fresh start.

42:13.239 --> 42:16.403
I didn't like my life here
and um...

42:18.661 --> 42:19.697
That's that.

42:29.130 --> 42:30.166
OK.

42:33.468 --> 42:35.425
So then why the fuck
did you call me today?

42:38.306 --> 42:39.217
Why are we doing this?

42:39.307 --> 42:41.720
Because, I really
wanted to see you.

42:41.809 --> 42:45.553
It's been a long time
and I wanted...

42:50.276 --> 42:52.359
I'm in town...

42:52.445 --> 42:56.029
And, I just couldn't leave
without seeing you.

42:56.657 --> 42:58.093
I love you...
I care about you a lot!

42:58.117 --> 43:01.030
You can't say that to me.
You can't...

43:02.997 --> 43:04.078
Fuck you!

43:06.084 --> 43:07.165
Fuck you.

43:14.342 --> 43:16.959
Adrian, we have known each other
since we were ten

43:17.053 --> 43:19.761
and this is how you're going to
fucking end this?

43:20.556 --> 43:21.763
I...

43:23.518 --> 43:25.180
I just wanted to see you
one last time.

43:29.023 --> 43:31.060
Well it looks like you
got what you wanted.

43:34.987 --> 43:36.194
You're a fucking coward.

43:42.411 --> 43:43.527
You're a piece of shit.

43:46.582 --> 43:48.289
I think you should go now.

43:58.010 --> 43:59.046
I'm really sorry, Carly.

44:15.153 --> 44:18.897
♪

44:43.556 --> 44:44.967
Oh shit, Mom!

44:45.141 --> 44:46.052
Language!

44:46.142 --> 44:48.885
Oh my God,
what are you doing in here?

44:48.978 --> 44:50.935
Your Dad was snoring up a storm

44:51.022 --> 44:52.684
and I came in here
to wait for you

44:52.773 --> 44:54.514
and I guess I just fell asleep.

44:55.276 --> 44:56.483
Where have you been?

44:57.403 --> 44:59.190
Um, I was hanging out
with Carly.

45:00.948 --> 45:03.031
Oh, did you have a good time?

45:06.579 --> 45:07.990
Oh honey,
you don't look very good.

45:08.623 --> 45:10.205
Yeah, no, I don't feel good.

45:10.291 --> 45:11.122
Have you been drinking?

45:11.209 --> 45:12.040
Mom...

45:12.126 --> 45:14.083
And you drove all the way
from Dallas,

45:14.170 --> 45:15.035
you could've killed someone!

45:15.129 --> 45:17.041
I'm not drunk, Mom, Jesus.

45:17.131 --> 45:18.338
Adrian!

45:18.424 --> 45:20.040
Oh my God...

45:20.134 --> 45:22.091
[retching]

45:32.230 --> 45:33.790
Let's hope it's
not another stomach flu.

45:36.943 --> 45:38.545
Maybe I should take you
to the doctor tomorrow.

45:38.569 --> 45:40.151
No, it's not a stomach flu.

45:42.531 --> 45:44.568
And, I'm actually starting
to feel a little better.

45:46.244 --> 45:48.361
Are you able to undress yourself
and get in the tub?

45:48.454 --> 45:49.570
Yeah, Mom.

45:58.631 --> 45:59.671
It smells like bubble gum.

46:01.509 --> 46:02.509
Just like childhood.

46:05.054 --> 46:06.511
Y'know you made
a bath for me

46:06.597 --> 46:08.088
every single time I'm sick.

46:08.599 --> 46:09.715
And I still do.

46:12.019 --> 46:14.011
I'm sorry, Mom,
I didn't mean to make you mad.

46:15.356 --> 46:16.517
I swear I'm not drunk.

46:19.318 --> 46:20.854
Is this about Carly?

46:22.488 --> 46:23.854
We had
a really big fight tonight.

46:25.825 --> 46:27.407
Pretty sure
that friendship's over.

46:27.827 --> 46:29.034
Oh nonsense.

46:29.996 --> 46:31.516
You guys have
known each other forever,

46:31.580 --> 46:34.163
it's not like it's the first
time you've had a fight.

46:34.917 --> 46:37.079
I'm sure you'll both
work through this.

46:40.381 --> 46:42.088
Mom, I'm never
gonna be with Carly.

46:45.594 --> 46:47.005
I need you to understand that.

46:54.979 --> 46:57.141
You should have your tea,
before it gets cold.

47:04.447 --> 47:06.466
I don't want you to think
we didn't like the presents

47:06.490 --> 47:08.072
you got for us.

47:08.159 --> 47:10.902
We're just, not used to
having such nice things.

47:12.663 --> 47:15.121
And you know, your Dad
is kind of a cheapskate.

47:15.416 --> 47:16.532
Oh, Mom.

47:19.545 --> 47:21.036
Well, he is.

47:25.009 --> 47:27.217
You're never gonna believe me
when I tell you this.

47:30.222 --> 47:31.303
What?

47:36.479 --> 47:38.562
I didn't vote
for Reagan last year.

47:39.190 --> 47:40.306
Mom!

47:40.983 --> 47:43.225
Your Dad has no idea.

47:43.319 --> 47:45.026
You voted for Mondale?

47:45.821 --> 47:47.904
You actually
voted for a Democrat?

47:48.949 --> 47:51.032
I changed my mind
at the last minute.

47:51.118 --> 47:55.158
I really liked his
nuclear freeze policy and...

47:55.247 --> 47:56.283
I don't believe in war.

47:57.500 --> 48:01.164
I saw what it did to your Dad,
and to his friends.

48:03.506 --> 48:05.668
And then there's
the Equal Rights Amendment.

48:07.218 --> 48:09.084
I just had a good feeling
about him.

48:15.184 --> 48:17.471
I didn't even know
you were that into politics.

48:17.937 --> 48:19.497
Sweetie, I'm not just
a country bumpkin.

48:20.815 --> 48:22.397
I like to think of myself as

48:22.483 --> 48:24.850
a well-informed citizen
these days.

48:36.163 --> 48:37.699
You think you're ready for bed?

48:38.666 --> 48:41.124
Um, I'm gonna stay here
another minute.

48:43.129 --> 48:44.245
OK.

48:47.383 --> 48:48.715
Thanks, Mom.

49:19.623 --> 49:20.784
<i>Adrian?</i>

49:21.375 --> 49:22.411
<i>Adrian.</i>

49:24.378 --> 49:25.994
Uh, yeah?

49:27.006 --> 49:28.126
<i>Get up, we're gonna be late.</i>

49:28.549 --> 49:31.383
<i>It's alright, just let him rest.
He's not feeling well.</i>

49:31.886 --> 49:34.094
<i>But Mom, he already said
he was gonna take me.</i>

49:36.599 --> 49:38.386
<i>Adrian? Can we go now?</i>

49:43.230 --> 49:45.017
Yeah, hey can you
just give me...

49:46.275 --> 49:47.475
Just give me like two minutes?

49:55.910 --> 49:58.197
Hey, can we have...

49:58.287 --> 50:00.324
one adult, one child for
<i>A Chorus Line,</i> please?

50:00.539 --> 50:01.905
Sorry, that one's sold out.

50:04.168 --> 50:06.501
I'm sorry, bud,
it's my fault we're late.

50:06.962 --> 50:11.502
It's OK. I wouldn't mind
seeing <i>Back to the Future.</i>

50:12.259 --> 50:13.579
How many times
have you seen that?

50:14.011 --> 50:15.877
I dunno, like, four?

50:15.971 --> 50:18.588
OK, let's see something
you haven't seen.

50:18.682 --> 50:19.682
OK...

50:20.476 --> 50:22.138
Oh. <i>Nightmare 2.</i>

50:22.603 --> 50:24.890
That's rated R.
I can't take you to see that.

50:24.980 --> 50:25.891
Mom and Dad will kill me.

50:25.981 --> 50:27.563
Mom and Dad don't have to know.

50:28.901 --> 50:29.982
Please?

50:35.241 --> 50:37.824
[movie plays]

51:06.480 --> 51:08.187
So, I think I'm gonna get these.

51:10.609 --> 51:12.396
You don't have to spend
your entire

51:12.486 --> 51:13.977
gift certificate today, buddy.

51:14.071 --> 51:15.903
Yeah, but they had
all the ones I wanted.

51:17.491 --> 51:18.607
Bud, you...

51:18.701 --> 51:22.991
Wow, you are listening to
way too much Top 40.

51:25.124 --> 51:27.662
Alright, we gotta get you
some different tapes...

51:29.336 --> 51:31.544
Do you know <i>The Cure?</i>

51:31.630 --> 51:32.871
Or <i>REM?</i>

51:32.965 --> 51:34.456
- Who?
- OK, let's go.

52:21.513 --> 52:22.594
Hey.

52:24.350 --> 52:26.057
You wanna have a drink?

52:26.143 --> 52:27.224
No, I'm good, thanks.

52:30.105 --> 52:31.185
Couldn't sleep either, huh?

52:32.983 --> 52:34.064
No.

52:35.527 --> 52:37.143
Come on, put that water down.

52:38.238 --> 52:40.104
Have a beer
with your old man, come on.

52:41.075 --> 52:42.407
Grab a seat.

52:46.246 --> 52:47.453
There ya go.

52:47.539 --> 52:48.700
Sit down.

52:53.671 --> 52:55.537
Have I ever had a drink
with you before?

52:55.631 --> 52:57.293
No, I don't think so.

52:58.926 --> 53:02.044
Hell, I was 15 when I first
had a beer with my Dad.

53:07.559 --> 53:08.640
Oh, well, cheers.

53:09.770 --> 53:10.886
Cheers, Dad.

53:19.446 --> 53:20.982
You...

53:21.073 --> 53:23.156
took off just as soon
as you could.

53:23.242 --> 53:24.608
You couldn't have...

53:24.702 --> 53:26.159
taken off any faster.

53:29.790 --> 53:31.497
Were you running away
from something?

53:34.128 --> 53:35.460
I wasn't running away, Dad.

53:39.425 --> 53:42.133
I can feel Andrew
drifting away from me.

53:44.555 --> 53:46.046
I don't even know
what to do about it.

53:48.600 --> 53:50.967
Everything was fine
when he was playing football.

53:51.061 --> 53:53.394
I was at every game.

53:54.148 --> 53:55.980
Once he started
to get into the theater,

53:56.066 --> 53:58.433
I just didn't know how
to talk to him anymore.

54:00.070 --> 54:02.232
Well, you can just...

54:02.322 --> 54:04.609
ask him questions about it,
that's a good place to start.

54:06.076 --> 54:08.614
He doesn't think I know
anything about that stuff,

54:08.704 --> 54:10.991
thinks I don't get it.

54:11.081 --> 54:12.617
Maybe he's right, I've...

54:12.708 --> 54:15.325
I've never been an
artsy-fartsy kind of guy anyway.

54:18.964 --> 54:20.421
But I am getting worried.

54:23.510 --> 54:24.967
Does he...

54:25.053 --> 54:26.214
Does he seem soft to you?

54:27.639 --> 54:28.971
He's still a kid, Dad.

54:29.057 --> 54:31.470
But you weren't like him
when you were at his age.

54:31.560 --> 54:34.678
You played sports
all through high school.

54:34.772 --> 54:36.308
You helped me out in the shop.

54:36.398 --> 54:38.685
I mean, Andrew's
gotta be a lot tougher

54:38.776 --> 54:41.314
or he's gonna have
a hard time out in the world.

54:42.571 --> 54:44.233
Your grandfather...

54:44.323 --> 54:45.985
Now he was tough on me.

54:46.074 --> 54:51.069
He didn't hug any of his sons,
or ask us questions.

54:52.956 --> 54:54.618
But he sure knew how to

54:54.708 --> 54:56.995
straighten us out
with discipline.

54:57.085 --> 54:59.953
Or a good ol' ass whoopin
if that's what was called for.

55:00.422 --> 55:02.584
I am who I am today
because of him,

55:02.674 --> 55:04.666
and I turned out alright,
didn't I?

55:05.886 --> 55:06.967
Yeah.

55:17.231 --> 55:19.188
You know you can always
count on me, right?

55:21.235 --> 55:25.525
If something goes wrong,
you need money, anything at all.

55:25.614 --> 55:28.652
We may not have much
but we always pull through.

55:30.202 --> 55:31.409
Hell...

55:31.495 --> 55:33.282
You wouldn't believe
some of the stuff I did

55:33.372 --> 55:36.115
for my buddies in 'Nam,
against them gooks.

55:36.208 --> 55:37.119
Dad, you can't say "gooks."

55:37.209 --> 55:39.166
I can call them
whatever the fuck I want!

55:40.671 --> 55:41.912
You weren't there.

55:44.550 --> 55:47.167
There were people's lives
depending on me.

55:47.261 --> 55:49.924
I've helped so many people.
I'm still known for that,

55:50.013 --> 55:52.676
you ask anyone in town.

55:52.766 --> 55:56.555
I'm the most reliable person
in this town. Ask anyone.

56:03.151 --> 56:04.187
So?

56:06.446 --> 56:07.653
Is everything OK with you?

56:11.577 --> 56:13.409
Come on now,
I don't have all damn night.

56:13.495 --> 56:14.736
Yeah, everything's fine.

56:25.090 --> 56:26.672
How'd you pay for the gifts?

56:29.678 --> 56:30.759
I've already told you guys.

56:31.346 --> 56:32.632
It's a lot of money, Adrian.

56:39.563 --> 56:41.520
I tried to call your office
a few months ago.

56:43.233 --> 56:44.394
Dad, you can't...

56:44.484 --> 56:47.773
You just... If you need to talk
to me you have to call my house.

56:47.863 --> 56:49.399
They don't like personal calls.

56:49.489 --> 56:51.606
I wondered why you wouldn't
give us your work number.

56:53.327 --> 56:55.284
But it didn't take me long
to figure that out.

56:59.499 --> 57:01.161
They said you don't
work there no more.

57:05.339 --> 57:07.331
Well, I'm not sure
who you talked to,

57:07.424 --> 57:10.041
it's a really big agency,
they were probably confused...

57:10.135 --> 57:11.751
Don't lie to me.

57:11.845 --> 57:13.086
What happened?

57:15.140 --> 57:18.349
I mean, did you get fired?
Did you steal something?

57:18.435 --> 57:19.516
Dad!

57:21.980 --> 57:23.346
Well, answer...
Answer my question!

57:25.400 --> 57:27.357
You may be a grown man
but I'm still your father.

57:27.444 --> 57:29.276
OK, I didn't steal anything!

57:31.031 --> 57:32.272
I can't...

57:32.366 --> 57:34.983
Honest... Oh, my God,
I gotta go to bed.

57:35.077 --> 57:37.569
You remember when I was in
Connecticut for Frank's funeral?

57:38.455 --> 57:40.117
He was the commander
of my platoon.

57:40.207 --> 57:41.323
- You remember?
- Yeah.

57:43.251 --> 57:44.492
Well...

57:50.217 --> 57:51.708
They thought he killed himself.

57:53.512 --> 57:55.720
Knowing him he just probably
just got too wasted.

57:57.057 --> 57:58.969
Fooling around
on some shooting range

57:59.059 --> 58:00.675
that he shouldn't have been on.

58:01.603 --> 58:02.639
Stupid son of a bitch.

58:05.983 --> 58:11.854
So I was in Connecticut
for Frank, and then I took...

58:11.947 --> 58:14.439
the train down to the city
to have lunch with you.

58:15.909 --> 58:16.740
Yeah.

58:16.827 --> 58:18.193
I asked if I could
see your place

58:18.286 --> 58:20.824
but you had excuses as to
why that wasn't a good idea.

58:20.914 --> 58:24.078
Dad, I just, didn't want you
to see what a mess it was.

58:24.167 --> 58:25.408
If I'd had time to clean it...

58:25.502 --> 58:27.539
Why are you
still bullshittin' me?

58:32.092 --> 58:33.628
I took a cab
to your neighborhood.

58:37.931 --> 58:39.297
I wanted to see where you lived.

58:45.147 --> 58:48.140
As we drove
past your building...

58:50.193 --> 58:53.106
I thought I saw you with some
guy on the steps

58:53.196 --> 58:55.609
but I wasn't sure at first
if it was you

58:55.699 --> 58:59.613
so I had the cab driver
go around the block again.

59:01.997 --> 59:03.204
This time I...

59:05.125 --> 59:06.286
I was sure it was you.

59:15.052 --> 59:16.668
You had your arms around him.

59:22.017 --> 59:23.508
I didn't even recognize you.

59:25.437 --> 59:26.997
It was like
you were a different person.

59:48.960 --> 59:51.703
Don't you even think
about telling your mother.

59:51.797 --> 59:54.039
You will break her heart.

59:56.635 --> 59:59.548
You hear me? Not one word.

01:00:00.931 --> 01:00:02.012
Yes, sir.

01:00:39.302 --> 01:00:40.383
Ow!

01:00:41.513 --> 01:00:43.004
Did you cut yourself?
Let me see...

01:00:43.098 --> 01:00:44.555
Yeah... Where are the Band-Aids?

01:00:44.641 --> 01:00:45.722
I'll get them.

01:01:09.457 --> 01:01:11.119
- There.
- I got it.

01:01:11.209 --> 01:01:12.409
Why won't you let me help you?

01:01:12.460 --> 01:01:14.122
I'm fine, Mom! I'm not a child!

01:01:30.687 --> 01:01:33.020
<i>Adrian?
Somebody's here to see you.</i>

01:01:42.908 --> 01:01:44.788
<i>You sure there's nothing
I can get for you, hun?</i>

01:01:44.826 --> 01:01:46.066
<i>Make you some tea or something?</i>

01:01:46.119 --> 01:01:47.530
<i>Oh no, I'm fine, Mrs. Lester.</i>

01:01:47.954 --> 01:01:49.320
<i>Please, call me Eileen.</i>

01:01:50.498 --> 01:01:51.989
Where's Mr. Lester?

01:01:52.500 --> 01:01:53.911
He's at the store with Andrew.

01:01:54.211 --> 01:01:55.211
Oh, OK.

01:01:57.547 --> 01:01:59.209
Ah, our man of the hour.

01:02:01.009 --> 01:02:01.874
Hey.

01:02:01.968 --> 01:02:03.049
Hi.

01:02:04.554 --> 01:02:09.174
I've got a chicken to put in the
oven so I'll leave you to it.

01:02:09.267 --> 01:02:10.849
Say hi to your parents for me

01:02:10.936 --> 01:02:12.663
and let me know if there's
anything I can do.

01:02:12.687 --> 01:02:13.973
I will, thank you so much.

01:02:14.064 --> 01:02:15.180
Alright.

01:02:16.608 --> 01:02:17.608
Don't be a stranger.

01:02:18.026 --> 01:02:19.142
I won't.

01:02:24.532 --> 01:02:26.273
I'm starving,
do you wanna grab a bite?

01:02:29.162 --> 01:02:31.324
Wow, this place
has not changed a bit.

01:02:32.999 --> 01:02:35.116
Remember we used to come here
whenever we were broke

01:02:35.210 --> 01:02:37.953
and we'd order
an extra large order of fries

01:02:38.046 --> 01:02:40.379
and get refills on the Coke?

01:02:40.465 --> 01:02:43.583
And leave no tip!
We were terrible.

01:02:45.387 --> 01:02:47.003
Hi, what can I get for y'all?

01:02:47.639 --> 01:02:49.722
Um, I'll have a Caesar salad
and a Diet Coke.

01:02:51.685 --> 01:02:53.893
And I'm just gonna have
a cup of coffee,

01:02:53.979 --> 01:02:55.641
cream and sugar.

01:02:56.273 --> 01:02:59.482
And we're gonna have an extra
large order of fries to split.

01:03:00.068 --> 01:03:02.060
OK, perfect.
I'll be right back with that.

01:03:06.533 --> 01:03:08.365
I'm really sorry...

01:03:08.451 --> 01:03:09.658
about the other night.

01:03:11.121 --> 01:03:12.407
I just don't...

01:03:12.497 --> 01:03:14.097
I don't wanna lose you
as a friend again.

01:03:18.253 --> 01:03:20.085
Yeah, me too, Carly, I'm...

01:03:24.467 --> 01:03:26.208
I've really missed you.
I just, um...

01:03:29.681 --> 01:03:32.094
I don't know if I'm gonna be
here this time next year.

01:03:37.397 --> 01:03:38.638
What do you mean?

01:03:45.822 --> 01:03:48.030
Leo passed away two months ago.

01:03:50.910 --> 01:03:52.071
In October.

01:03:55.915 --> 01:03:57.372
Nine months
after he was diagnosed.

01:04:01.421 --> 01:04:03.083
We'd spent every
New Year's Eve together

01:04:03.173 --> 01:04:04.630
since we met.

01:04:05.383 --> 01:04:08.217
I was really hoping he was
gonna make it to this one.

01:04:12.557 --> 01:04:15.721
I called his parents up
after he died.

01:04:19.564 --> 01:04:21.164
They didn't want
anything to do with him.

01:04:25.945 --> 01:04:27.811
He really wanted
to be buried in Ohio,

01:04:27.906 --> 01:04:29.442
where he was born.

01:04:29.532 --> 01:04:31.148
I wasn't even able
to do that for him.

01:04:36.956 --> 01:04:38.492
I've lost so many friends.

01:04:40.210 --> 01:04:41.701
I've been to
six funerals this year.

01:04:44.422 --> 01:04:46.163
I feel like I'm losing
my fucking mind.

01:04:50.011 --> 01:04:51.468
Leo left me his Chihuahua.

01:04:53.390 --> 01:04:56.133
It breaks my heart a little bit
when he looks at me funny.

01:04:56.226 --> 01:04:58.513
He's still wondering
where Leo is.

01:05:01.606 --> 01:05:03.598
And uh...

01:05:03.691 --> 01:05:06.354
My job at the agency,
I lost that.

01:05:10.448 --> 01:05:12.128
Someone might have found out,
I don't know.

01:05:14.077 --> 01:05:16.160
And uh,
I'm working at a restaurant.

01:05:17.539 --> 01:05:21.123
Barely getting by, I spent all
my money on Christmas gifts.

01:05:24.003 --> 01:05:26.620
I can't believe it took you
this long to tell me.

01:05:28.633 --> 01:05:29.633
Did you really think that

01:05:29.717 --> 01:05:31.083
I wasn't gonna be cool
with that?

01:05:31.177 --> 01:05:32.177
Yeah.

01:05:35.432 --> 01:05:37.799
I guess we're even.
You don't really know me either.

01:05:40.478 --> 01:05:42.265
Promise me something.

01:05:44.065 --> 01:05:47.934
When you get sick,
you have to call me. OK?

01:05:49.946 --> 01:05:51.426
You don't wanna be
anywhere near this.

01:05:53.032 --> 01:05:54.364
Trust me...

01:05:56.077 --> 01:05:57.357
Things are gonna
get really ugly.

01:05:58.621 --> 01:06:01.079
I shouldn't have kissed you.
If something happened to you...

01:06:02.000 --> 01:06:04.162
Stop it, OK, stop it.
You're being paranoid.

01:06:05.336 --> 01:06:06.417
OK?

01:06:07.130 --> 01:06:08.416
I'm gonna see you
next Christmas.

01:06:09.299 --> 01:06:11.339
We're gonna go out and
we're gonna have a good time.

01:06:11.634 --> 01:06:13.394
And who knows,
there might be a cure by then.

01:06:14.429 --> 01:06:16.109
There could be new drugs,
new treatments...

01:06:16.181 --> 01:06:17.461
I'm not gonna make it that long.

01:06:19.642 --> 01:06:22.476
You're still healthy.
You don't even look sick to me.

01:06:46.044 --> 01:06:47.205
Sorry.

01:07:00.600 --> 01:07:02.557
You don't have to
say yes to this.

01:07:05.980 --> 01:07:06.980
But in the future...

01:07:10.235 --> 01:07:12.272
Would you tell Andrew what
really happened to me?

01:07:14.739 --> 01:07:15.855
Please?

01:07:30.588 --> 01:07:33.296
Honey, will you do us the honor?

01:07:35.009 --> 01:07:36.170
Uh, yeah sure.

01:07:41.349 --> 01:07:43.181
Dear Father...

01:07:43.268 --> 01:07:44.429
Um...

01:07:46.396 --> 01:07:49.104
Thank You
for another wonderful meal.

01:07:51.401 --> 01:07:53.142
And we wanna thank You

01:07:53.236 --> 01:07:55.979
for allowing us to spend
this Christmas together.

01:07:59.033 --> 01:08:02.071
We pray that there are many
more days like this to come,

01:08:02.161 --> 01:08:05.245
and many more memories
for us to look forward to.

01:08:09.377 --> 01:08:11.915
And we pray that...

01:08:12.005 --> 01:08:13.917
You'll continue
to teach us how

01:08:14.007 --> 01:08:15.623
to love
each other unconditionally,

01:08:15.717 --> 01:08:17.709
just the way that You love us.

01:08:20.555 --> 01:08:22.261
We pray that
Your everlasting grace

01:08:22.348 --> 01:08:25.307
continues to lead
and inspire us. Amen.

01:08:25.393 --> 01:08:26.474
(All) Amen.

01:08:29.479 --> 01:08:30.390
That was lovely.

01:08:30.481 --> 01:08:32.017
Thanks, Mom.

01:08:32.108 --> 01:08:34.191
Can't you just
stay a few more days?

01:08:35.361 --> 01:08:38.069
I really wish I could, Andrew,
but I have to get back to work.

01:08:41.367 --> 01:08:44.154
So, when are you
gonna come home next?

01:08:44.370 --> 01:08:45.986
Um, well...

01:08:49.292 --> 01:08:50.783
The next chance that I get.

01:08:52.002 --> 01:08:53.460
Better not be
another three years.

01:08:53.546 --> 01:08:56.788
I mean, you have a promotion
now, you make money,

01:08:56.883 --> 01:08:58.444
can't you just fly home
whenever you want?

01:08:58.468 --> 01:08:59.834
Let it go, Andrew.

01:09:20.323 --> 01:09:22.609
Hey.

01:09:24.243 --> 01:09:25.734
What's going on?

01:09:31.459 --> 01:09:33.121
I'll tell him for you.

01:09:35.004 --> 01:09:36.336
I'll tell Andrew.

01:09:39.634 --> 01:09:40.966
Thank you, Carly.

01:09:44.180 --> 01:09:45.261
Thank you.

01:10:04.992 --> 01:10:07.154
<i>I told you
I don't need a new coat.</i>

01:10:07.370 --> 01:10:10.204
<i>Honey, he's leaving soon.
Would you just put it on?</i>

01:10:10.289 --> 01:10:11.329
<i>It's the least you can do.</i>

01:10:11.416 --> 01:10:12.577
<i>Would you stop pestering me?</i>

01:10:12.667 --> 01:10:14.954
<i>If you won't put it on for him
then just put it on for me.</i>

01:10:15.044 --> 01:10:16.205
<i>Eileen?</i>

01:10:16.295 --> 01:10:17.295
<i>God, you're so stubborn.</i>

01:10:19.424 --> 01:10:21.144
<i>Why don't you just
take it to work with you?</i>

01:10:21.217 --> 01:10:23.800
<i>It's supposed to get cold later.</i>

01:10:26.389 --> 01:10:28.301
I'm sorry
I have to go again, bud.

01:10:29.392 --> 01:10:30.803
Are you gonna miss me?

01:10:36.107 --> 01:10:37.188
Alright.

01:10:38.484 --> 01:10:41.022
Wish I could bring you with me,
but you're just too big.

01:10:52.331 --> 01:10:54.197
I gotta go to work early
so your Mom's gonna

01:10:54.292 --> 01:10:55.578
take you to the airport.

01:10:55.668 --> 01:10:56.533
Alright.

01:10:56.627 --> 01:10:58.664
So, I'll say my goodbyes now.

01:11:02.300 --> 01:11:04.508
- Take good care of yourself.
- You too, Dad.

01:11:04.594 --> 01:11:05.960
I meant what I said.

01:11:07.555 --> 01:11:09.171
You can always count on me.

01:11:11.058 --> 01:11:12.174
OK...

01:11:12.268 --> 01:11:13.268
Hey, Dad.

01:11:13.686 --> 01:11:14.847
Yeah?

01:11:16.272 --> 01:11:18.152
I was reading through
some passages in the Bible

01:11:18.232 --> 01:11:20.519
that you and Mom got me and...

01:11:25.323 --> 01:11:26.683
I know I need to
make some changes.

01:11:30.369 --> 01:11:32.361
I'm a little lost
right now, but...

01:11:35.082 --> 01:11:37.699
With His light,
I know I can find my way back.

01:11:59.398 --> 01:12:00.934
I gotta go.

01:12:01.025 --> 01:12:02.186
Alright.

01:12:04.070 --> 01:12:05.070
Bye, Dad.

01:12:14.539 --> 01:12:15.620
Andrew...

01:12:17.500 --> 01:12:18.616
Andrew?

01:13:00.209 --> 01:13:01.325
Mom?

01:13:41.417 --> 01:13:42.498
Is it time?

01:13:42.585 --> 01:13:44.076
Yeah, we should get going.

01:14:01.395 --> 01:14:04.138
OK, I'm just gonna
drop you here.

01:14:05.441 --> 01:14:07.103
And I'm...

01:14:07.193 --> 01:14:08.900
I'm not gonna walk you in, OK?

01:14:09.195 --> 01:14:10.195
OK.

01:14:12.323 --> 01:14:14.235
I don't want you
to miss your plane.

01:14:25.127 --> 01:14:26.493
You know...

01:14:27.672 --> 01:14:30.380
You don't have to tell me,
until you're ready.

01:14:35.262 --> 01:14:37.049
And I'll try to be ready
when you are.

01:14:41.769 --> 01:14:43.385
[sobbing]
Mom...

01:14:58.285 --> 01:14:59.446
Alright...

01:15:01.998 --> 01:15:03.489
I should probably get going.

01:15:05.960 --> 01:15:07.121
OK.

01:15:42.830 --> 01:15:44.196
I love you, Mom.

01:15:45.082 --> 01:15:46.118
I love you, too.

01:17:29.145 --> 01:17:30.977
(Adrian on tape)
<i>Hey, Andrew...</i>

01:17:31.063 --> 01:17:33.521
<i>Now I want you to keep this
tape as long as possible.</i>

01:17:35.151 --> 01:17:38.690
<i>I think you might need to listen
to this again in the future.</i>

01:17:38.779 --> 01:17:41.021
<i>It might make more sense
to you when you're older.</i>

01:17:42.908 --> 01:17:44.399
<i>You're gonna have
some tough days.</i>

01:17:46.203 --> 01:17:47.319
<i>Days where...</i>

01:17:49.081 --> 01:17:51.198
<i>You'll feel like
everything sucks.</i>

01:17:52.168 --> 01:17:54.080
<i>And you don't wanna
get out of bed.</i>

01:17:55.379 --> 01:17:58.463
<i>Days where you're gonna feel
like you just don't belong.</i>

01:17:59.550 --> 01:18:00.757
<i>I've had a lot of those days.</i>

01:18:02.678 --> 01:18:03.678
<i>And I want you to know...</i>

01:18:05.806 --> 01:18:07.926
<i>You're not the only one who
feels the way that you do.</i>

01:18:10.227 --> 01:18:12.389
<i>There's a whole world out there
for someone like you.</i>

01:18:13.522 --> 01:18:16.606
<i>I promise you, you are not as
different as you think you are.</i>

01:18:18.527 --> 01:18:20.439
<i>And Mom and Dad,
they might not get it.</i>

01:18:22.239 --> 01:18:24.105
<i>A lot of your friends
might not get it either.</i>

01:18:25.034 --> 01:18:28.698
<i>And some of them might say some
pretty mean and awful things.</i>

01:18:29.747 --> 01:18:30.988
<i>Because they just don't get it.</i>

01:18:32.708 --> 01:18:33.949
<i>But I get it.</i>

01:18:35.002 --> 01:18:38.586
<i>And I know that you're
gonna learn to be happy...</i>

01:18:38.672 --> 01:18:39.753
<i>with who you are.</i>

01:18:41.550 --> 01:18:43.917
<i>And you may need to be
in another place to be happy.</i>

01:18:44.011 --> 01:18:45.377
<i>And you know what?
That's OK.</i>

01:18:45.471 --> 01:18:47.258
<i>That's why I left home.</i>

01:18:47.348 --> 01:18:49.465
<i>It might seem like the
hardest thing to do at first.</i>

01:18:50.768 --> 01:18:53.135
<i>But it might be
the right thing for you too.</i>

01:18:54.563 --> 01:18:56.020
<i>And in another time...</i>

01:18:57.691 --> 01:18:59.023
<i>At another place...</i>

01:19:01.111 --> 01:19:02.471
<i>You're gonna meet
the right people.</i>

01:19:04.240 --> 01:19:06.197
<i>People that are just like you.</i>

01:19:07.701 --> 01:19:09.158
<i>People that are just like me.</i>

01:19:10.537 --> 01:19:11.653
<i>So hang in there, Andrew.</i>

01:19:12.706 --> 01:19:14.493
<i>Things tend to
get a little darker</i>

01:19:14.583 --> 01:19:15.949
<i>before they get brighter.</i>

01:19:17.670 --> 01:19:19.753
<i>I will always regret
that I wasn't home enough</i>

01:19:19.838 --> 01:19:21.329
<i>these past few years.</i>

01:19:21.840 --> 01:19:24.127
<i>I feel like I'm only
really getting to know you</i>

01:19:24.218 --> 01:19:25.459
<i>this time around.</i>

01:19:27.346 --> 01:19:29.178
<i>And I'm proud
that you're my brother.</i>

01:19:32.685 --> 01:19:34.176
<i>I will always be with you.</i>

01:20:51.138 --> 01:20:53.676
(Radio) <i>We know that there is
no forgiveness in hell.</i>

01:20:53.766 --> 01:20:56.349
<i>Whatever goes to hell,
will stay in hell...</i>

01:20:56.435 --> 01:20:57.642
[clicks off radio]

01:21:18.749 --> 01:21:20.957
(Intercom) <i>Attention passengers
of Flight 261</i>

01:21:21.043 --> 01:21:22.750
<i>to New York, LaGuardia.</i>

01:21:22.836 --> 01:21:25.044
<i>We are now boarding
groups A and B.</i>

01:21:26.215 --> 01:21:27.735
<i>Please have your
boarding passes ready.</i>

01:21:28.592 --> 01:21:31.380
<i>Again, we are now boarding
groups A and B.</i>

